   "body" : "Besides Windows platform, `pkg-config` works well for both system Qt and Qt in `depends`.\r\n\r\nBut there are some pitfalls when using different Qt versions that are downloaded with [Qt Online Installer](https://www.qt.io/download-qt-installer), e.g.:\r\n- #7714\r\n- [QTBUG-73151](https://bugreports.qt.io/browse/QTBUG-73151)\r\n- [QTBUG-80922](https://bugreports.qt.io/browse/QTBUG-80922)\r\n\r\nCurrently, there is no way to bypass `pkg-config` workflow for downloaded Qt (on non-Windows platforms). I have to use a patch to bypass `pkg-config` on testing purpose.\r\n\r\nIt seems to be useful for developers and testers to have an additional `configure` option, say `--with-qt-dir`, which forces to bypass `pkg-config` workflow.\r\n\r\nFor example:\r\n```\r\n./configure --with-gui=qt5 --with-qt-dir=/home/hebasto/Qt/5.14.0/gcc_64\r\n```\r\n\r\nMore refs:\r\n- #8314\r\n- #17768",
